git for [<options>] [--] <command> - Evaluate a shell command in [current repo and] submodules.

    -h|--help               show this help
    -q|--quiet              don't print submodule name before evaluating command
    -r|--recursive          traverse submodules recursively
    -s|--sm-only            traverse submodules only (skip working directory)
    -e|--stop-on-error      stop looping as soon as command fails (exit code != 0)
    -b|--bottom-up          traverse submodule tree bottom up (default to top down)
    <command>               command to be evaluated
                            the command has access to $name, $sm_path, $displaypath, $sha1 and $toplevel
example:
    git for -q 'echo $path `git rev-parse HEAD`'
    git for -q 'git vstatus -q'
